  schema:name "Totality and Mereology: The Problem of the Whole and All-That-Is" ;
  schema:description "A philosophical survey of the whole, the concept of 'everything,' and frameworks for understanding how parts relate to wholes. From Leśniewski's mereology through set theory, Russell's paradox, and relational accounts of totality in Whitehead, Buddhist philosophy, and Indigenous ontologies." ;
